Hey @leandrosilvaferreira,

It looks like we added support for TLS on Redis outside of this with `QUEUE_BULL_REDIS_TLS`, Our implementation does mean that you will need to have valid certificates in use but I suspect that will ok if it is redis from a larger provider.

@pa-sundae I know you made this PR a while ago but it looks like we missed this when adding support recently as part of a larger project so for now I am going to close this PR, If we decide to add support for invalid certificates though I will try and makes sure we use this as a base.

@blanxii thanks for taking a look at this PR 😊 

to provide some context: since we don't provide nor ship an SMTP service we just want to check if our SMTP communication is correct. We do that through testing with an external SMTP service, however this service can (and is unfortunately) be down at times. In this case our tests would fail which wouldn't be due to our wrong SMTP-logic or anything, but simply because of a third party. We looked into test tagging etc. which is unfortunately not supported by jest. Therefore @ivov decided to mitigate the problem short-term with this PR until we find a more long-term solution.

hope this sheds some light on why we are doing this

hey @Joffcom @janober 🙂

the base structure of the node is ready and working. for now, it can send text, media, and basic templated messages (although Wapp's API is buggy as mentioned in the description). There are 3 things still missing that I will keep working on:

1. trigger node
2. template components: template messages can have what the [spec](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/whatsapp/cloud-api/reference/messages#template-object) refers to as components, which can be passed to dynamic templates (`hello {{1}}`)  by adding the following parameters to the template property:
```json
"components": [
    {
        "type": "body",
        "parameters": 
        [
            {
                "text": "world",
                "type": "text"
            }
        ]
    }
]
```
I am trying to figure out what would be the best way to include this in n8n. what I thought is doing something like in the switch node, in this case, you would add x amount of components and parameterize them. I will keep on working on this one and lmk if you have any suggestions
3. media management: use WhatsApp's API to manage business' media

